A teenager died after falling from scaffolding in York city centre, an inquest has heard.Harry Calam, 19, suffered a traumatic brain injury in the fall on Little Stonegate in on 24 June.Jonathan Heath, senior coroner for York and North Yorkshire, said the teenager's death had been confirmed at the scene.The inquest at Northallerton Coroner's Court was adjourned for a full inquest to take place at a later date.
